[Review by copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]]: ## Pull request overview

This PR aims to fix pixel-level misalignment between the renderer-side placeholder/screenshot and the main-process `WebContentsView` by snapping layout geometry to the physical pixel grid and switching the viewport element to explicit absolute positioning.

**Changes:**
- Snap computed viewport size and position using the host zoom factor in `BrowserEditor.layoutBrowserContainer`, and explicitly set `left/top` inline.
- Update CSS so the `.browser-container` is absolutely positioned within its wrapper (with size/position driven by JS) and adjust placeholder screenshot sizing behavior.
- Remove per-feature snapping from emulation layout computation so snapping happens in one place.

<details open>
<summary>Show a summary per file</summary>

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/browserView/electron-browser/media/browser.css | Makes the browser container absolutely positioned and updates screenshot background sizing; adds new toolbar action modifier selectors. |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/browserView/electron-browser/features/browserEditorEmulationFeatures.ts | Removes zoom-factor snapping from emulation viewport computation (snapping moved to editor layout). |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/browserView/electron-browser/browserEditor.ts | Snaps container size and screen position to the host zoom grid and applies explicit `left/top` positioning before notifying the model. |
</details>

